cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.PL

The paper describes an algorithmic differentiation library designed for machine learning applications, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The library also provides high-performance linear algebra primitives, which could place it in the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category. The fact that the library is implemented in F# and exposes higher-order functions suggests that it could also belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. The development of a transformation-based version of the library using F#'s code quotation metaprogramming facility could place it in the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category. Finally, the mention of a CUDA-based GPU backend suggests that it could also belong to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category.
